Package: btorrent
Architecture: linux-any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Concurrent BitTorrent client
 btorrent is a command-line BitTorrent client for Linux by Saeed Hany.
 It uses an epoll-based scheduler to manage concurrent peer connections
 and implements rarest-first piece selection with block-level pipelining.
 .
 Features: DHT peer discovery, magnet links (BEP 9/10 metadata fetch),
 seeding, Peer Exchange (BEP 11), rate limiting, resume, endgame mode,
 and file locking to prevent simultaneous instances.
 .
 Protocols: BEP 3, 5, 9, 10, 11, 12, 15.
